Here are some useful CSS style properties you can use on the website

In VSCode there should be a big autofill list as you type,
so that should make it easier to edit them.


Colors
background-color: red;              
border: 5px solid red;

Text
font-family: 'Arial';
font-size: 20px;
font-color: red;
text-align: center;

Sizing
width: 51%; (or can be width: 22px;)
height: 51%;  (or can be height: 22px;)
padding: 30px;
margins: 40px;

Positioning elements inside of a seciton is done using this:
display: flex;
justify-content: center;
